Manchester United are hopeful that Robin van Persie’s ankle injury will only keep him out for one game, which is good news for Louis van Gaal but not for Radamel Falcao.

Van Persie limped out of United’s defeat at home to Southampton on Sunday and was forced to cancel plans to travel to Zurich for the Ballon d’Or awards ceremony where he had been nominated for Goal of the Year.

However, tests have revealed no serious damage and Van Persie is only expected to be ruled out of this weekend’s game at QPR. 

